name: Power Stilts
description: As with similar localities deemed worthy of preservation in Charleston, Port Royal and all the way down to Jacksonville, they had eventually been placed on hydraulic platforms. So Old Savannah still looked remarkably as it had in the nineteenth and twentieth centuries, except that the warm Atlantic shallows now flowed sleepily beneath the power stilts that kept the historical city high and dry. From The Human Blend by Alan Dean Foster. Published by Del Rey in 2010. Artwork was created using https://artbreeder.com. Artbreeder app was created by Joel Simon https://www.joelsimon.net/
